  "description": [
    "We have been invited by a resolution of the third general assembly of this State to call a convention for the pur pose of amending or changing the con etitution And it is not denied but that j it lias for its object the introduction ol Slavery among us The question is I fairly before the people whether they will aid or assist in the introduction ol unlimited and unqualified slavery into this state or not Let us here pause and inquire by what authority the people of Illinois would make this great and essential change in her internal policy As early as 1787 the Congress of the United States declared in a compact between the people of the United States and the people of the north western territory of which Illinois formed a part that there shall be neither slavery nor involuntary servitude in the said territory otherwise than in the punishment of crimes where of the party shall have been duly con victed This pledge was offered to all persons who should emigrate hither hat this state should ever remain free end that it should be an asylum to all those who should withdraw from the slavery of"
